EOH, Iliad Africa, Metair, Mvelaphanda: South African Stock Market Preview

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-03-15T05:50:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/eoh-iliad-africa-metair-mvelaphanda-south-african-stock-market-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index fell to its lowest
since Dec. 1, sliding 295.28, or 1 percent, to 30,878.58, at the
5 p.m. close of trade in Johannesburg.    EOH Holdings Ltd. (EOH)  : The information-technology
provider is scheduled to report first-half earnings. Shares in
the company fell 24 cents, or 1.4 percent, to 17.50 rand.    Iliad Africa Ltd. (ILA)  : The producer of building
supplies is expected to announce its annual earnings. Shares in
the company gained 1 cent, or 0.1 percent, to 7.01 rand.    Metair Investments Ltd. (MTA)  : The company, which
produces automobile parts, reports its full-year earnings.
Metair’s shares were unchanged at 13.30 rand.    Mvelaphanda Group Ltd. (MVG)  : The commercial-services
provider said it expects to report a loss per share of 51 cents
to 56 cents for the six months to Dec. 31, compared with a
profit of 117.3 cents a year earlier. The company also said it
has entered into talks, which if successfully concluded, may
affect its share price. Mvelaphanda’s stock advanced 1 cent, or
0.3 percent, to 3.11 rand.    Sovereign Food Investments (SOV)  Ltd: The poultry
producer said its offer of shares to existing shareholders was
oversubscribed by 25 percent. Shares in the company declined 15
cents, or 2.8 percent, to 5.30 rand.    Steinhoff International Holdings Ltd. (SHF)  : Africa’s
largest furniture maker said it raised an aggregate amount of
467.5 million euros ($651.2 million), before expenses, in its
oversubscribed convertible bond offer. Shares in the company
fell 3 cents, or 0.1 percent, to 24 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 0.5 percent to $25.08.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) was unchanged at $47.04. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) dropped 0.8 percent to $74.24. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) fell 1.2 percent to $4.78. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) gained 0.6 percent to $17.48. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY
US) declined 0.6 percent to $12.40. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) fell 1.3 percent to $28.19. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US) lost
0.8 percent to $5.02. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) rose 0.1 percent to
$53.15.  To contact the reporter on this story:
